==Tailoring==
Wild Plum can be used in the spool of the [[2 Willow Lane#Sewing Machine|Sewing Machine]] to create the dyeable [[Tailoring#Pants|Farmer Pants]].  [[File:Farmer Pants.png|36px]] It can be used in [[dyeing]], serving as a purple dye at the dye pots, located in [[Emily]]'s and [[Haley]]'s house, [[2 Willow Lane]].

==Quests==
*The Wild Plum may be randomly requested in [[Fall]] at the [[Quests#Help Wanted Quests|"Help Wanted" board]] outside [[Pierre's General Store]] for a reward of {{Price|240}} and 150 [[Friendship]] points.

==History==
{{History|1.0|Introduced.}}
{{History|1.1|Labeled as a fruit, allowing it to be made into [[wine]] and [[Jellies and Pickles|jelly]].}}
{{History|1.4|Changed from Forage to Fruit in Brazilian-Portuguese, Chinese, German, Japanese, Spanish, and Russian.  Can now be used in [[Tailoring]].}}

